FBIS4-43076 "drweu113_o_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-113 Daily Report 11 Jun 1994 CYPRUS Spokesman Avoids Comment Spokesman Avoids Comment NC1106111794 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network in Greek 1030 GMT 11 Jun 94 NC1106111794 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network Greek BFN [Excerpt] There has been no official reaction to the report carried by REUTER that President Glavkos Kliridhis expressed the intention to resign if the UN Security Council decides to continue talks on the confidence-building measures. The government spokesman avoided making any comment and said that the letters that the president has sent to President Clinton and British Prime Minister John Major are confidential. REUTER reported that President Kliridhis' threat to resign is outlined in these letters. [passage omitted]
